pusillus [sic] G. M. Allen, 1917, 
<materialsCitation pageId="7" pageNumber="441">
“Arroyo Salado, 
<collectingRegion box="[762,985,1780,1813]" country="Dominican Republic" name="Santo Domingo" pageId="7" pageNumber="441">Santo Domingo</collectingRegion>
,” 
<collectingCountry box="[1015,1310,1780,1813]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="7" pageNumber="441">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[761,1354,1705,2129]" lastBlockId="7.[144,1354,2135,3234]" pageId="7" pageNumber="441">
<taxonomicName box="[762,895,1819,1852]" class="Mammalia" family="Mormoopidae" genus="Pteronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="441" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pteronotus</taxonomicName>
pusillus was formerly classified as a subspecies of P. parnellir, but here it is considered a distinct species. Fossil subspecies gonavensis, described by K. F. Koopman in 1995 from an owl pellet deposit found in a cave near En Café, Gonave Island, off western Hispaniola,is considered a temporal variation of the population currently inhabiting Hispaniola (i.e. P. pusillus). Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
